{"id": "EUVD-2025-12922", "enisaUuid": "fe91e3bd-c806-3d36-b566-a9aed423e394", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: wwan: iosm: fix memory leak in ipc_wwan_dellink\n\nIOSM driver registers network device without setting the\nneeds_free_netdev flag, and does NOT call free_netdev() when\nunregisters network device, which causes a memory leak.\n\nThis patch sets needs_free_netdev to true when registers\nnetwork device, which makes netdev subsystem call free_netdev()\nautomatically after unregister_netdevice().", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T14:10:19", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T16:04:38", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49867", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/128514b51a5ba2c82f9e4a106f1c10423907618a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2ce2348c2858d723f7fe389dead9b43b08e0944e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f25caaca424703d5a0607310f0452f978f1f78d9"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49867", "GHSA-2crp-r6g2-9c5p"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "14d98f45-c2df-3e16-95d4-2e52903e8000", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2a54f2c7793409736f2e5ea101e050b3f1997088 <2ce2348c2858d723f7fe389dead9b43b08e0944e"}, {"id": "402cfa2e-3c47-3730-a9e4-954cb7a91f60", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "70b1a2bc-f761-3a9d-a37c-e27315bc8fce", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2a54f2c7793409736f2e5ea101e050b3f1997088 <128514b51a5ba2c82f9e4a106f1c10423907618a"}, {"id": "864df8f6-1e3f-3f69-8f11-e5bc3e7891af", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.79"}, {"id": "b3ff8abf-031e-32b3-92a5-070eb8a896b6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "bd449ca2-3166-3868-b229-a426aec41c28", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.9"}, {"id": "e29df1b2-3d99-3